divs: sighting detailsi was standing in my back yard, facing west, looking at the stars. i saw several prop planes flying with their lights blinking and could hear their engines. i then noticed a very bright object coming from the west\southwest. it made no noise and was going in a perfectly straight line to the east\northeast. it looked like a star, but was even more brilliant the venus. it was white with spikes of light coming out of it like a car headlight coming at you in the rain? spikey, i guess. i first thought it was a plane. the light was as bright as a planes landing lights. but i noticed it didn't have blinking lights like a plane and was completely silent. i watched it until it faded from view to the east. it didn't quit shining, it seemed to fade with the distance and ground lights from the city. i went from puzzlement to being perplexed, then shock when i realized it wasn't a plane. it was too low and far to bright to be a satellite. it seemed just a little higher than the other planes in the area, maybe 500 or so feet.
Summary: brilliant star-like object travelling west to east, silent, no flashing lights
